esident of both Point Reyes and the Truckee Tahoe area.\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Point_Reyes\", \"score\": 0.9999999949232006, \"rank\": 5.076897532868379e-09, \"text\": \"Point Reyes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Point_Reyes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Point_Reyes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Palisades Tahoe spokesperson said the slide happened around 9:30 a.m. on the Palisades side of the mountain, above the GS bowl area of KT-22.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The KT-22 lift had just opened on Wednesday for the first time this winter, and this area serves expert skiers.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 100 search and rescue personnel combed the area to see if anyone was injured or trapped.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A man was killed and another injured in an avalanche at the Palisades Tahoe ski resort on Wednesday morning.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Tahoe\", \"score\": 0.999999736166081, \"rank\": 2.637480099862318e-07, \"text\": \"Tahoe\", \"types\": [\"Q23397\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Tahoe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Tahoe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sgt.\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David Smith, a spokesperson for the Placer County sheriff, said hours later that a man died, and another person sustained non-life-threatening injuries.\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Smith_(sculptor)\", \"score\": 0.9066412690011675, \"rank\": 0.03557403557403617, \"text\": \"David Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Smith_(sculptor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Smith_(sculptor)\"}, {\"begin\": 959, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Placer_County,_California\", \"score\": 0.9999999971385023, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Placer County\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Placer_County,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Placer_County,_California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic Valley Fire Chief Brad Chisholm said the injured person suffered a lower leg injury.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chisholm_Trail\", \"score\": 0.9993060898945011, \"rank\": 0.0006943917416534004, \"text\": \"Chisholm\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chisholm_Trail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chisholm_Trail\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our thoughts and prayers are with their family members at this difficult time,\\\" said the sheriff's office in a statement.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The resort and adjoining Alpine Meadows ski slopes will be closed due to the avalanche.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpine_Meadows_(ski_resort)\", \"score\": 0.8178432547660074, \"rank\": 0.22272727272728596, \"text\": \"Alpine Meadows\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpine_Meadows_(ski_resort)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpine_Meadows_(ski_resort)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a very sad day for my team and everyone here,\\\" said President and CEO Dee Byrne over the tragedy.\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Byrne\", \"score\": 0.9943327270921918, \"rank\": 0.0056995735570228205, \